cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper discusses techniques for generating degrees of belief from a knowledge base consisting of both objective information and degrees of belief. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), social and information networks (cs.SI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, given the focus on generating degrees of belief, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories.
